Stoke boss Mark Hughes has claimed Tom Jones is costing them a spot in the Europe League via the Fair Play League .
The Potters ' faithful have been singing Jones ' song ` Delilah ' as their unofficial club anthem since the 1980s .
And Hughes believes his side are being harshly marked down because of the 1960s song .
Stoke are top of the Premier League Fair Play table and are set to miss out on European football next year .